{
  "query": "What are the observed effects of fitting deterrents, such as lights or electropositive materials, to fishing gear?",
  "relevant_summary": "Studies have examined various deterrents fitted to fishing gear with mixed results. For electropositive deterrents, two of four replicated controlled studies found that fishing gear fitted with electropositive deterrent materials caught fewer unwanted spiny dogfish, longnose skate, sharks and rays, and fewer undersized halibut compared to standard fishing gear (Action 2696). However, the other two studies and a global systematic review found that electropositive deterrents resulted in similar catches of unwanted spiny dogfish, sharks, blue shark and sharks and rays compared to gear with no deterrents (Action 2696). Regarding behavior, three of four studies found that electropositive materials reduced feeding attempts and bait consumption of spiny dogfish, great hammerhead and draughtboard sharks, while one study found no reduction in bait consumption by bonnethead and young lemon sharks (Action 2696). For light-based deterrents, one study found that shrimp trawl nets with artificial lights caught fewer unwanted fish when fitted to the fishing line but not to a size-sorting grid (Action 2695). Another study found that LED lights on a size-sorting grid did not improve size-selectivity of long rough dab, Atlantic cod, haddock and redfish (Action 2695). Four controlled studies found that gillnets with LED lights, light sticks or UV lights caught fewer green turtles and loggerhead turtles than nets without lights, while one study found mixed effects of increasing light sticks on longlines for catching loggerhead and leatherback turtles (Action 3554). One study found that no loggerhead turtles were caught and died in gillnets with UV lights whereas some did in nets without lights (Action 3554). Visual deterrents showed that gillnets with floating shark shapes caught fewer green turtles than unmodified nets (Action 3553).",
  "action_ids": [
    "2696",
    "2695",
    "3554",
    "3553"
  ]
}

